<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-01-24T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-01-24T12:00:00-05:00" n="197" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7353b W 52/200: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-01-24T17:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">January 24,
                                        1924—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 8:20
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>6. Chamber of Deputies has just approved finally Western Union contract.
                            Report by mail. Embassies London and Rome informed. Please inform
                            Newcomb Carlton in reply his letter 10th to me.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>